{
  "message": "test(corpus): add golden fixtures for 3 high-fanout rate_limit rules\n\nBefore this change, three critical-severity rules in the rule packs had\nzero positive corpus coverage. Every one of them feeds a workflow that\ndrives automation, so silent regressions would route users into the\nwrong remediation path:\n\n* `codex.rate_limit.detected` \u2192 `handle_usage_limits`\n* `claude_code.rate_limit.detected` \u2192 `handle_claude_code_limits`\n* `gemini.rate_limit.detected` \u2192 `handle_gemini_quota`\n\nAdded 3 positive fixtures (each using an agent-specific unique anchor \u2014\n\"429 Too Many Requests\" for Codex, \"HTTP 529\" for Claude Code,\n\"RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED: quota exceeded\" for Gemini \u2014 plus a retry_after\nphrase that the rule's capture group extracts). Inputs were crafted to\navoid collisions with sibling rules in the same pack (the initial Claude\nCode fixture containing \"overloaded\" was rewritten to keep the fixture\nfocused on the rate_limit rule only).\n\nAdded 3 near-miss fixtures asserting the rate_limit rule does NOT fire\non healthy-operation text, which protects against regex over-broadening\nregressions.\n\nGolden contents were captured from the live engine output via\n`cargo test --test pattern_corpus`, reviewed for correctness (rule_id,\nseverity, event_type, extracted.retry_after capture group value), and\nblessed.\n\nVerified: `cargo test -p frankenterm-core --test pattern_corpus\ncorpus_fixtures_match_expected` \u2192 `test result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed`\nunder `--no-default-features --features mcp,asupersync-runtime` at\n/tmp/ft-pane6-target.\n\nCoverage delta: rules with \u22651 positive fixture went from 33 to 36\n(out of 41 non-test rules); rules with zero positive coverage dropped\nfrom 5 to 2 (the remaining two are `wezterm.pane_exited` and\n`codex.usage_reached`, both of which appear to be legacy ID aliases\nof rules that ARE covered under the canonical spelling).",
